{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-page-js","path":"/config/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>The configuration parameter is an object passed as an argument to the function which is exported by this package.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">shell <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">require</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"shell\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\napp <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">shell</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>config<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"the-root-properties\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#the-root-properties\" aria-label=\"the root properties permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" fill=\"#fff\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>The root properties</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"./commands/\"><code class=\"language-text\">commands</code></a> (object|array, optional)<br>\nGroup the arguments into multiple sections. Support object and array notation. If defined as an object, keys correspond to the \"name\" properties. If defined as  an array, the \"name\" property is required.</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">description</code> (string, optional)\nThe description of the application.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/usage/extended/\"><code class=\"language-text\">extended</code></a> (boolean, optional, false)<br>\nSwitch the format of the data between the simple flatten mode and the safer extended mode.</li>\n<li><a href=\"./router\"><code class=\"language-text\">router</code></a> (object, optional)<br>\nAn object configuring the router plugin with low level properties.</li>\n<li><a href=\"./load/\"><code class=\"language-text\">load</code></a> (function|string, optional)<br>\nFunction or a module referencing the function to load modules, the default implementation ensure modules starting with './' are relative to\n<code class=\"language-text\">process.cwd()</code> and use <code class=\"language-text\">require.main.require</code>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"./main/\"><code class=\"language-text\">main</code></a> (object, optional)<br>\nAnything left which is not a parameter at the end of the arguments.</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">name</code> (string, optional)\nThe name of the application, used by the help plugin to display information.</li>\n<li><a href=\"./options/\"><code class=\"language-text\">options</code></a> (object|array, optional)\nDefined the expected command options, sometimes called flags.</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">route</code> (function|string, optional)<br>\nExecute a function or the function exported by a module if defined as a  string, provide the params object, see the <a href=\"/api/route/\">routing documentation</a>.</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">strict</code> (boolean, optional, false)<br>\nDisable auto-discovery.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"initialisation\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#initialisation\" aria-label=\"initialisation permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" fill=\"#fff\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Initialisation</h2>\n<p>The configuration is commonly passed as the main argument when initialising <code class=\"language-text\">shell</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> shell <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">require</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'shell'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> app <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">shell</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  name<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'my_new_app'</span>\n  main<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'some_param'</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>app<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">parse</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>It is however easy to externalize the configuration into an external file stored on the file system. JSON being natively handled by Node.js, here is how an application could rely on a configuration file stored in \"/etc/my<em>new</em>app.json\":</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> config <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">require</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'/etc/my_new_app'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> shell <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">require</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'shell'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> app <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">shell</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>config<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>app<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">parse</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>","frontmatter":{"title":"Configuration","keywords":["shell","node.js","cli","usage","config","configuration"],"description":"Configuration object for passing as an argument to the function"},"fields":{"edit_url":"https://github.com/adaltas/node-shell/edit/master/content/config/index.md","slug":"/config/"},"headings":[{"value":"The root properties","depth":2,"id":"the-root-properties"},{"value":"Initialisation","depth":2,"id":"initialisation"}]}},"pageContext":{}},"staticQueryHashes":["1387919533","63159454"]}